                    "type": "entries",
                    "name": "Age",
                    "entries": [
                        "Dwarves reach adulthood in their early teens and typically live for a century."
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "type": "entries",
                    "name": "Alignment",
                    "entries": [
                        "Most Stone dwarves are lawful, believing firmly in the benefits of the caste system, with a strong sense of racial superiority. Surface born dwarves tend towards no particular alignment, as they are typically raised in human societies."
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "type": "entries",
                    "name": "Size",
                    "entries": [
                        "Dwarves stand between 4 and 5 feet tall and average about 150 pounds. Your size is Medium."
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "type": "entries",
                    "name": "Speed",
                    "entries": [
                        "Your base walking speed is 25 feet."
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "type": "entries",
                    "name": "Darkvision",
                    "entries": [
                        "Originating from the Stone, the dwarven race has developed superior vision in dark and dim conditions. You can see dim light within 60 feet of you as if it were bright light, and in darkness as if it were dim light. You can't discern color in darkness, only shades of gray."
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "type": "entries",
                    "name": "Detached from the Fade",
                    "entries": [
                        "Dwarves are completely cut off from the Fade, and as such, cannot be mages or become possessed by demons."
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "type": "entries",
                    "name": "Child of the Stone",
                    "entries": [
                        "Dwarves are born of the earth itself, and as such gain a natural resistance to magic. You have advantage on saving throws against spells and other magical effects. Additionally, you are immune to the side effects of raw lyrium."
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "type": "entries",
                    "name": "Dwarven Combat Training",
                    "entries": [
                        "You have proficiency with the battleaxe, handaxe, light hammer, and warhammer."
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "type": "entries",
                    "name": "Tool Proficiency",
                    "entries": [
                        "You gain proficiency with an artisan tool of your choice."
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "type": "entries",
                    "name": "Stonecunning",
                    "entries": [
                        "Whenever you make an Intelligence (History) check related to stonework and minerals, you are considered proficient in the History skill and add double your proficiency bonus to the check."
                    ]
                }
            ]
